records.addlTxt:
Defendant Kendron Romal Bolden in court with attorney Richard E. Thomey.  William P. Dockry appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered count dismissed and read-in for sentencing purposes.

AS TO COUNT 2:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by:  Defendant sentenced to serve 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 MONTHS.  Probation may be transferred to Brown County, if accepted.
Conditions: 
*  Pay restitution in the amount of $199.65 to MPD by December 22, 2016 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  Successfully complete a course in anger management;
*  Serve 20 days in the House of Correction; sentence stayed and to be used at the discretion of the agent;
*  No contact with WTMJ at 720 W Capitol Drive;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges by December 22, 2016 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.  
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
